1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,640
 - Hello, now we're gonna talk about the other half

2
00:00:02,640 --> 00:00:04,860
 of the views, the templates.

3
00:00:04,860 --> 00:00:08,620
 So the templates are our way of creating HTML.

4
00:00:08,620 --> 00:00:12,780
 And again, just to ground everything that we've got here,

5
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:15,480
 you know, we're in the views, and the views are really

6
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:17,820
 sort of the code, the Python code that we drive.

7
00:00:17,820 --> 00:00:20,820
 We're gonna get the forms in a bit, but views kind of

8
00:00:20,820 --> 00:00:24,220
 merge stuff from the templates, merge stuff from the models,

9
00:00:24,220 --> 00:00:27,660
 put, you know, send stuff in and make pages, right?

10
00:00:27,660 --> 00:00:30,260
 So this is going to look a lot like HTML.

11
00:00:30,260 --> 00:00:34,300
 It doesn't have to be HTML, it can be things but,

12
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:37,260
 other than HTML, but templates in our class

13
00:00:37,260 --> 00:00:41,180
 will mostly be HTML, and so they're kind of the last

14
00:00:41,180 --> 00:00:44,860
 little piece of the puzzle to start building user interfaces.

15
00:00:44,860 --> 00:00:47,880
 And from this point on, we're going to be, you know,

16
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:51,000
 making user interfaces rather than introducing the parts

17
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,100
 of a Django application that have the user interface.

18
00:00:54,100 --> 00:00:57,760
 So this is the text from the Django website.

19
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:01,580
 You know, it's about convenient ways to generate

20
00:01:01,580 --> 00:01:04,700
 HTML dynamically, and there's a couple of different

21
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:07,420
 templating engines, we're using the default one,

22
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:11,660
 and there is some data that we pass into the template.

23
00:01:11,660 --> 00:01:13,860
 There's a process that's called rendering,

24
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,780
 and then we get the HTML back, and we return to the browser

25
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:20,760
 with that HTTP response, which we've already been doing.

26
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:23,780
 It's not, the request-response cycle is the same.

27
00:01:23,780 --> 00:01:26,040
 The difference is, instead of writing Python code

28
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:28,260
 to concatenate a bunch of things together,

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:31,060
 we are going to use a template engine.

30
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:33,440
 So this is the kind of stuff that we've been doing all along.

31
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:36,860
 We have a class and a view, a view class,

32
00:01:36,860 --> 00:01:40,340
 REST main view that extends this view.

33
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:42,300
 In comes perhaps the request object,

34
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,460
 and then maybe even another parameter.

35
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:46,720
 That's not changing.

36
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:49,020
 What we're doing here is we're using concatenation.

37
00:01:49,020 --> 00:01:51,100
 Concatenation, these little plus signs.

38
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,580
 Escaping, we're doing all the escaping and concatenating,

39
00:01:53,580 --> 00:01:56,020
 and then we are sending back a response.

40
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:57,620
 So what goes back as a response,

41
00:01:57,620 --> 00:02:00,200
 what comes in as a request, what goes back as a response.

42
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:02,780
 We're still gonna do that, we're just gonna

43
00:02:02,780 --> 00:02:05,360
 get rid of that middle bit and make it a little prettier

44
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:07,360
 and make it a little more sense.

45
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:11,240
 If you look at that, oops, if you look at that,

46
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:13,700
 if you look at it, you gotta get it syntactically right.

47
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:17,180
 You got indentation problems, that's three lines of Python.

48
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:19,180
 I'm using triple quotes, I'm using plus,

49
00:02:19,180 --> 00:02:22,200
 I gotta get all that matching together.

50
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,940
 And then eventually, the HTML is going back,

51
00:02:25,940 --> 00:02:27,600
 I'll be using single quotes, double quotes,

52
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,220
 and all those kinds of things.

53
00:02:29,220 --> 00:02:31,820
 And JavaScript's gonna look really ugly here.

54
00:02:31,820 --> 00:02:34,320
 Indenting of the HTML kind of will fight

55
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,720
 with the indenting of the Python.

56
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:39,400
 So this is just general, I mean, I've only done short ones,

57
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,600
 'cause I only wanted to show you a little bit

58
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,400
 before we showed you templates.

59
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,900
 So the basic process is a bit of software,

60
00:02:45,900 --> 00:02:50,040
 a template software that Django provides us.

61
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:52,880
 We're using the built-in Django one.

62
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:55,180
 And basically template is some HTML

63
00:02:55,180 --> 00:02:58,520
 with some hotspots in it that says put data here.

64
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,720
 And then the rest of it is just HTML.

65
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:05,020
 And then we pass the data in, in some kind of an object,

66
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:06,660
 you know, dictionary, et cetera.

67
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:10,720
 And then a bit of code pulls all that stuff together

68
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:15,020
 and then produces the HTML with all the data placed in it.

69
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:17,000
 Often the render data that we're passing

70
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,220
 and it's coming from a model, for example.

71
00:03:19,220 --> 00:03:20,880
 You know, we might talk to a database,

72
00:03:20,880 --> 00:03:24,020
 load up a bunch of rows, and then put it in.

73
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:26,720
 But in the simplest form, what we've got

74
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:28,500
 is we've got like a little dictionary,

75
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:32,200
 call this the context, you could call it the render data,

76
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,300
 and then you have the render template.

77
00:03:34,300 --> 00:03:36,200
 So the render template is really HTML,

78
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,940
 and that's what makes it a lot easier to look at,

79
00:03:38,940 --> 00:03:40,800
 because you're not putting double quotes around anything,

80
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:44,460
 there's no concatenation, but there are special characters.

81
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:47,600
 And what the double curly brace surrounding it says

82
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:51,340
 is instead of that, take this bit out and replace it

83
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:54,720
 with whatever's in the variable dat from the render data.

84
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:57,400
 And so that's how, when it's all said and done,

85
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:59,980
 this is replaced in the fun stuff,

86
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:03,840
 replaces curly brace, curly brace dat in the final output.

87
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,480
 And if you thought about it for a while,

88
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,040
 you could probably write a render engine.

89
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:08,440
 They're not that hard.

90
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:10,700
 Now you'll see they have some sophisticated features

91
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:12,340
 eventually, so you probably don't want to write

92
00:04:12,340 --> 00:04:14,700
 your own render engine, but you could imagine

93
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:18,740
 a Python assignment where I say write me a function

94
00:04:18,740 --> 00:04:20,740
 that takes a dictionary that looks like that,

95
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:24,320
 and then with key value dat fun stuff,

96
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:26,540
 and then take some text file, has curly brace,

97
00:04:26,540 --> 00:04:28,680
 curly brace dat, curly brace, curly brace,

98
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:31,600
 and then find that and then replace it with that string.

99
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,300
 You could write that code.

100
00:04:33,300 --> 00:04:34,600
 You don't want to write that code.

101
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,240
 Django has already written that code for you.

102
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,820
 So here's the code in action.

103
00:04:38,820 --> 00:04:41,860
 And so this is, we're gonna call this,

104
00:04:41,860 --> 00:04:45,520
 we're in the application named tmpl, temple.

105
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:49,500
 And so we have the application temple,

106
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:52,360
 we have the view game, and then we have a number 200,

107
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:55,120
 and that's what we put in our urls.py

108
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:58,400
 to route the game view and take one parameter.

109
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:01,240
 Remember that slugs are a special version of strings

110
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:04,120
 that are letters, numbers, and dashes, I believe.

111
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:07,280
 And so the entire request coming in from the browser

112
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:09,220
 is coming into the variable request.

113
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:12,140
 This number 200 is coming in the variable,

114
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:15,260
 from the url is coming in the variable guess.

115
00:05:15,260 --> 00:05:19,500
 And so instead of us concatenating together,

116
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:21,960
 we are going to create a context.

117
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:24,180
 What I call a context was just as a dictionary

118
00:05:24,180 --> 00:05:25,900
 of key value pairs.

119
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:29,460
 And the key for guess is g-u-e-s-s, it's a string.

120
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:32,080
 That guess will matter inside the template.

121
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:33,840
 And then we pull this number 200

122
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:36,640
 and we convert it to an integer, and then we pass it in.

123
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:39,500
 And this render, we pass it the request object,

124
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,940
 we pass it the name of a template,

125
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:45,880
 and then we pass the context, the key value pairs,

126
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:48,160
 to be substituted in that.

127
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,800
 So let's take a look.

128
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:52,320
 So if we look at this template,

129
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:55,340
 it has a series of curly brace like hotspots,

130
00:05:55,340 --> 00:05:58,960
 places where you would replace stuff.

131
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:01,360
 And so the double curly brace just says

132
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:04,800
 retrieve the string that is under guess and put it in,

133
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,800
 and so that's how we get your guess was 200

134
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,420
 in the ultimate output.

135
00:06:09,420 --> 00:06:11,860
 And then we have curly brace percent

136
00:06:11,860 --> 00:06:13,800
 all the way to percent curly brace,

137
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:16,280
 and this is a series of if then else's.

138
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,760
 So you can put logic in here too.

139
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:21,240
 You don't have to just take this string and put it in.

140
00:06:21,240 --> 00:06:22,960
 So what we're doing is we're basically saying

141
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:26,080
 if the guess is less than 42, we print out too low.

142
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:29,360
 If it's above 42, we print too high.

143
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:32,280
 And of course, if it is 42, we print out just right.

144
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,000
 And since our guess was 200,

145
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,000
 it prints out too high.

146
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:41,640
 And so basically this makes this view code a lot simpler

147
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:44,280
 and doesn't put a less than's and greater than's

148
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,600
 and concatenations.

149
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:48,460
 It's all substituted by this render routine.

150
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:51,960
 Now the render routine returns an HTTP response request,

151
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:54,640
 so when we get that back, we just return it.

152
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:57,940
 So we hand back to Django the HTTP response request,

153
00:06:57,940 --> 00:07:01,940
 and then the page is displayed in our browser.

154
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:05,180
 And remember that we have a Django project,

155
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:06,720
 and this is the Django project.

156
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:09,520
 In my case, the Django project is djfree-samples,

157
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:12,240
 and I have a bunch of little applications.

158
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,760
 All these things, as a matter of fact,

159
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:16,060
 Temple is the one we're working at right now.

160
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:18,840
 Those are just the different pieces of sample source code

161
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:21,440
 that I've built for this class to talk about.

162
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:23,800
 And so those are applications.

163
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:26,480
 So it's just that Django terminology.

164
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:29,920
 Project made up of one or more applications and folders.

165
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,540
 Okay.

166
00:07:31,540 --> 00:07:33,660
 And so the problem is, is these templates,

167
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:37,800
 when Django starts up based on the settings.py,

168
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,640
 it loads all these files up.

169
00:07:39,640 --> 00:07:41,140
 Loads them all up.

170
00:07:41,140 --> 00:07:44,140
 And so it loads them all up,

171
00:07:44,140 --> 00:07:46,840
 and the templates are actually global,

172
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:48,000
 and we'll see this in a bit.

173
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,140
 They're global across all of the applications.

174
00:07:51,140 --> 00:07:55,300
 And so the problem is, is that if you have a template name

175
00:07:55,300 --> 00:08:00,040
 like detail.html, and you have a whole bunch of applications

176
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,780
 like I do, all of which wanna have a template name

177
00:08:02,780 --> 00:08:05,640
 detail.html, it doesn't work.

178
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:09,620
 'Cause which detail.html, it'd be template/detail

179
00:08:09,620 --> 00:08:12,000
 in two folders, it's not clear which one

180
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,840
 you're talking about.

181
00:08:13,840 --> 00:08:16,040
 So we've adopted a convention that we take

182
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:18,860
 the application name, and we make a subfolder

183
00:08:18,860 --> 00:08:21,800
 inside of templates that's the application name,

184
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:25,720
 and then we use this fabs/detail.html,

185
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:29,440
 or pics/detail.html as the name of the template.

186
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:32,240
 So in a sense, we're introducing a subfolder,

187
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,960
 and it's a little jarring at first,

188
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,060
 'cause you see it's the same.

189
00:08:36,060 --> 00:08:37,320
 It's a good convention.

190
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:40,880
 I mean, it's unfortunate we have to have the convention,

191
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:43,680
 but because these names end up being global

192
00:08:43,680 --> 00:08:47,700
 across your entire Django project in each application,

193
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:51,480
 and to get them a name, to get them properly named,

194
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:55,400
 it's necessary to introduce this extra level of redirection.

195
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,280
 We get the logins, there's templates that are stored

196
00:08:58,280 --> 00:09:00,920
 outside in other applications, so sometimes you wanna

197
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:02,800
 get a template in some other application,

198
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:07,040
 so there's all kind of reasons this is a great idea.

199
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:08,920
 It just isn't the prettiest thing in the world.

200
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,840
 So just, when you see it, don't freak out,

201
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:15,540
 I try to call it out in the slides.

202
00:09:15,540 --> 00:09:17,780
 And so we put these paths that includes

203
00:09:17,780 --> 00:09:20,160
 the application name twice.

204
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:23,640
 It's weird, but it is necessary to do this

205
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:27,960
 because of the notion that all these template names

206
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:30,440
 are global across the entire application,

207
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:32,600
 but if then we called this the template name

208
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:35,560
 with the name of the application prefixed, away it goes.

209
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,440
 Django could've made that a little easier for us,

210
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:40,880
 but they basically didn't, and so we have to do this.

211
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:43,720
 But everybody does it the same way.

212
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,800
 So now what I wanna talk about is

213
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,440
 the actual templating language itself.

214
00:09:47,440 --> 00:09:49,920
 I showed you a couple examples, the double curly braces,

215
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,740
 but it turns out there are lots of things

216
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:53,680
 that you can do with double curly braces

217
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,040
 in the template language.

218
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:57,960
 (jazz piano music)

